<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{y}=-{1}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{9}{y}={36}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({3},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{1}{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{1}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{1}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{\left(\frac{{-{1}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}\right)}+{9}{y}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{3}}{{-{{2}}}}\cdot{\left(-{1}\right)}--\frac{{3}}{{-{{2}}}}{\left({1}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.5}-{\left(-{1.5}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.5}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}={36}--{1.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.5}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}={37.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1.5}+{\left({9}\right)}\right)}{y}={37.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7.5}{y}={37.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{37.5}}{{7.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{1}{\left({5}\right)}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{\left({5}\right)}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{1}-{\left({5}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{6}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

